          I thought Chelsea did well. More chances created, more shots on target and got it tactically right albeit slightly over-cautious at the begin. The 2nd PSG goal killed the tie. I think away goals should count but only after extra time. Willian was good again, 1 of only a couple of Chelsea players who can hold his head up high this season. Hazard is clearly not the other one. Chelsea should sell him, and Oscar, and bring in some match-tough players. Too many times I see Eden hiding unwilling to take the risks which truly world class players do. Chelsea, like Arsenal and Juventus, will think they're unlucky to draw such a big club so early in the knockout round (probably a SF now depending on the subsequent draws) when Wolfsburg v Gent comprises 1 of the other L16 ties. Sorry but that is Europa league all day long.
